# Implementation Plan - Phase 6: Markdown Support and Final Polish

This plan covers the installation of markdown shortcuts, file download mechanics, keybinding managers, responsive styling, title auto-save triggers, live character/word counts, empty-state dashboard listings, and final developer review guides.

## Proposed Package Additions (Frontend)
- `tiptap-markdown` (Integrates markdown parsing, input rules, and markdown serialization within Tiptap)

---

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend Components

#### [MODIFY] [DocumentEditor.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/pages/DocumentEditor.jsx)
- Import `Markdown` extension from `tiptap-markdown` and register it inside the Tiptap Editor instance.
- Add "Export as Markdown" (.md) and "Export as Plain Text" (.txt) action buttons in the toolbar.
- Implement file download triggers using `Blob` data structures and `URL.createObjectURL()`.
- Register keyboard shortcuts for manual saving, undo, redo, and typographic toggling (Bold, Italic, Underline).
- Attach an `onBlur` callback to the document title input, calling the title-update API to save titles automatically when the user clicks away.
- Build a live status indicator showing: "Saved just now" or "Saving..." depending on socket save events.
- Append a footer containing live word and character counters using the Tiptap editor character counting helpers (or simple text length queries).
- Implement responsive CSS wrappers that collapse collaborative elements into a neat layout on mobile devices.

#### [MODIFY] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///e:/Vishal%20Folder/codec%20intern/Collaborative%20Document%20Editor/frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx)
- Create a beautiful, polished empty-state template if the loaded documents list length is zero.
- Display a modern illustration, friendly guidance text, and a prominent "Create your first document" call to action.

